wlrGenTable.name: wlrGenTable
wlrGenTable.description: Generic Roaming information for a collection of WaveLAN interfaces attached to a particular system.

wlrGenEntry.name: wlrGenEntry
wlrGenEntry.description: Generic Roaming information for a particular WaveLAN interface.

wlrGenIndex.name: wlrGenIndex
wlrGenIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies a WaveLAN network interface this roaming information applies to. The interface associated with a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

wlrDomainId.name: wlrDomainId
wlrDomainId.description: The Domain Identifier identifies the (multi-cellular) roaming service domain. Mobile stations will connect only to those access points that have the same DomainId as they have been configured with themselves. (note: Value '0000'H has a special meaning; it may be used to disable roaming)

wlrBeaconKey.name: wlrBeaconKey
wlrBeaconKey.description: The key used to encipher the WaveLAN NWID when included as data in the Beacon message.

wlrMsTable.name: wlrMsTable
wlrMsTable.description: Mobile station roaming information for a collection of WaveLAN interfaces attached to a particular system.

wlrMsEntry.name: wlrMsEntry
wlrMsEntry.description: Mobile station roaming information for a particular WaveLAN interface.

wlrMsIndex.name: wlrMsIndex
wlrMsIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies a WaveLAN network interface this roaming information applies to. The interface associated with a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

wlrRetryLimit.name: wlrRetryLimit
wlrRetryLimit.description: The protocol retry limit for the handover procedure.

wlrNumberOfRecovers.name: wlrNumberOfRecovers
wlrNumberOfRecovers.description: The number of Recover requests to be sent after an unsuccessful handover procedure.

wlrCommsQuality.name: wlrCommsQuality
wlrCommsQuality.description: The Communications Quality to the current access point. This is the running average maintained by the driver software. Expressed as percentage of maximum possible.

wlrCurrentApName.name: wlrCurrentApName
wlrCurrentApName.description: The name of the current access point this mobile station is connected to.

wlrMsSignOnFailures.name: wlrMsSignOnFailures
wlrMsSignOnFailures.description: The number of times no timely response was received to the Sign-on request protocol message during the sign-on and handover procedures.

wlrMsHandovers.name: wlrMsHandovers
wlrMsHandovers.description: The number of times a handover has been initiated. (i.e. Sign-on request sent, not re-sent).

wlrMsHandoverFailures.name: wlrMsHandoverFailures
wlrMsHandoverFailures.description: The number of times a handover procedure failed due to not receiving a response to the Sign-on requests and retries got exhausted.

wlrMsBeaconsMissedNormal.name: wlrMsBeaconsMissedNormal
wlrMsBeaconsMissedNormal.description: The number of Beacons missed from current access point(s), during normal mode.

wlrMsBeaconsMissedSearch.name: wlrMsBeaconsMissedSearch
wlrMsBeaconsMissedSearch.description: The number of Beacons missed from current access point(s), during regular search mode.

wlrMsRegularCellSearchEntered.name: wlrMsRegularCellSearchEntered
wlrMsRegularCellSearchEntered.description: The number of times the regular cell search mode was entered from the normal mode.

wlrMsFastCellSearchEntered.name: wlrMsFastCellSearchEntered
wlrMsFastCellSearchEntered.description: The number of times the fast cell search mode was entered.

wlrMsTimeInNormalMode.name: wlrMsTimeInNormalMode
wlrMsTimeInNormalMode.description: The total time in normal (i.e. non-cell-search) mode since the roaming functionality got initialized. (in seconds)

wlrMsTimeInRegularSearchMode.name: wlrMsTimeInRegularSearchMode
wlrMsTimeInRegularSearchMode.description: The total time in Regular Cell Search Mode since the roaming functionality got initialized. (in seconds)

wlrMsTimeInFastSearchMode.name: wlrMsTimeInFastSearchMode
wlrMsTimeInFastSearchMode.description: The total time in Fast Cell Search Mode since the roaming functionality got initialized. (in seconds)

wlrApTable.name: wlrApTable
wlrApTable.description: Access point roaming information for a collection of WaveLAN interfaces attached to a particular system.

wlrApEntry.name: wlrApEntry
wlrApEntry.description: Access point roaming information for a particular WaveLAN interface.

wlrApIndex.name: wlrApIndex
wlrApIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies a WaveLAN network interface this roaming information applies to. The interface associated with a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

wlrStopCellSearchThreshold.name: wlrStopCellSearchThreshold
wlrStopCellSearchThreshold.description: The level of communications quality on which the mobile station stops looking for other access point(s). Expressed on percentage-scale. Should be greater than wlrRegularCellSearchThreshold + 3.

wlrRegularCellSearchThreshold.name: wlrRegularCellSearchThreshold
wlrRegularCellSearchThreshold.description: The level of communications quality on which the mobile station starts looking for an access point with a level of communications quality higher than the Stop Cell Search Threshold. Expressed on percentage-scale. Should be smaller than wlrStopCellSearchThreshold - 3, and greater than wlrFastCellSearchThreshold + 3

wlrFastCellSearchThreshold.name: wlrFastCellSearchThreshold
wlrFastCellSearchThreshold.description: The level of communications quality on which the mobile station starts looking for an access point with a level of communications quality higher than this threshold. Expressed on percentage-scale. Should be smaller than wlrRegularCellSearchThreshold - 3

wlrBeaconInterval.name: wlrBeaconInterval
wlrBeaconInterval.description: The Beacon interval time. In units of a hundredth of a second (1/100 s, or 10 ms).

wlrBeaconTimeout.name: wlrBeaconTimeout
wlrBeaconTimeout.description: The Beacon time-out value. In units of a hundredth of a second (1/100 s, or 10 ms). Should be at least 2 * wlrBeaconInterval.

wlrApSignOnRequests.name: wlrApSignOnRequests
wlrApSignOnRequests.description: The number of Sign-on Requests received.

wlrApHandoversSent.name: wlrApHandoversSent
wlrApHandoversSent.description: The number of times a handover has been requested from an other Access point.

wlrApHandoversReceived.name: wlrApHandoversReceived
wlrApHandoversReceived.description: The number of times a mobile station has been handed over to an other access point.
